Write a shell script, mySysInfo.sh, to list out your system specs and state. The script should be run on each of the VMs mentioned above and output the following info in a readable format.

    1. System Name, IP Address and Date
    
    2. System uptime
        Operating system
    
    3. Hardware configurations
    
    4. CPU  type and Number of cores
    
    5. Main Memory Size
    
    6. Hard disk size
        Total Number of partitions and their size
        Disk used
        Free space in Disk

    7. Instantaneous RAM and CPU usages/loads
    
    8. Total number of  jobs running in the system
        No. of jobs running in kernel space
        Number of jobs running in user space

    9. List of user accounts and List of users currently logged in.
